---- Verdict ----
NCNN Vulkan backend runs cleanly on Mali-G78 (Pixel 6 Tensor G1) — no patch needed,
fp16/int8 paths available, cooperative matrix unsupported.  Compared to 4-thread
CPU benchncnn, the comparison per workload is above.  Memory-bandwidth bound
quantized models (like llama.cpp LLMs) gain nothing or regress.  Vision CNNs with
heavy fp16 matmul can win on GPU — see per-model speedups in the tables above.

